2. In the sending fragment (`FragmentA`), create an instance of your custom class and put it into a `Bundle`:

```java
public class FragmentA extends Fragment {
    // ...

    private void openFragmentB() {
        FragmentB fragmentB = new FragmentB();

        // Create an instance of your custom class
        MyData myData = new MyData("John Doe", 30);

        // Create a Bundle object
