2. In the `onCreate()` method of the fragment, the values are extracted from the `Bundle` using `getString()` and `getInt()`.
3. An instance of `MyData` is created using the constructor, passing the values from the `Bundle`: `myData = new MyData(name, age);`.
4. Alternatively, you can create an instance of `MyData` using the default constructor and set the values using the setter methods: `myData.setName(name); myData.setAge(age);`.

After creating the `MyData` object, you can use it in your fragment or pass it to other classes or fragments as needed.

